## Workflow

- Non-trivial work goes through the flow plugin: /flow:spec → owner
  approval → /flow:implement (fresh session) → /flow:accept → owner
  accepts. Trivial changes (one-sentence diff, no dependents) skip the
  lifecycle.
- When the owner requests non-trivial work without mentioning flow,
  offer to start /flow:spec before writing any code — one line, not a
  lecture. If the owner declines, proceed normally.
- Worktree sessions: persistent memory is unavailable — openspec/ and
  CHANGELOG.md carry the work state; this file carries only standing
  facts and the bounded Current state block. Merge back to main when a
  phase completes.
- If the flow plugin is unavailable in this session (cloud VM, fresh
  machine), follow the lifecycle shape manually: openspec change → owner
  approval → TDD implementation on a branch → full checks + fresh-context
  review → owner accepts.
- Never commit or push unless explicitly asked.

